place.name: STRATFIELD TURGIS
place.gazetteerText: STRATFIELD-TURGIS, a parish in Basingstoke district, Hants; 3¼ miles SE by S of Mortimer r. station, and 5¾ NE by N of Basingstoke. Post town, Stratfieldsaye, under Winchfield. Acres, 909. Real property, £1,661. Pop., 195. Houses, 40. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Winchester. Value, £410.* Patron, the Duke of Wellington. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
